          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            There is zero chance of Bayern playing this formation against Arsenal, although I hope they do. With Bayern's personnel, 4-3-3 is ideal (and was Real Madrid's best formation under Carlo). The Christmas tree was a great formation 10-15 years ago and helped Carlo achieve great success, but there is a reason it has hardly been used for 8 years. The front 6 of Alonso, Thiago, Vidal, Coman, Lewandowski and Costa would cause problems for any defence. Ancelotti is a brilliant tactician but sometimes he out-thinks himself. Bayern fans had enough of that under Pep.
